 just before the mob hit, an ooc from someone already at the fort that a Flicker of Sea was rotting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> !<br>
<br>
New strategy, and I believe this will work for single lower mages.  Invis and run all the way into fort, there seems to be enough room to avoid aggroing the mobs around the wall of the fort although the 2 guards outside building with luggalds might aggro (they were cleared when I drug corpse in).  I looted mages corpse, CoTH cleric in for rez (he did not get aggro in this spot at 52, though the guards by building were down as mentioned).<br>
<br>
I waited about an hour for the Necro to finish his fun with no Flicker of Sea drop for him. My turn came and in the first round it dropped, gated and waited for a porter to show up to head to Lavastorm. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=429815">Talena Waterflower</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - 55 Myrmidon<br>
